The map view provides an interactive geographic visualization of your campaign leads, zones, interactions, and sales.

## Accessing Map View

1. Navigate to your campaign
1. Click the **Map** tab
1. The map loads with campaign data

## Map Interface

### Map Display

The map shows:

- **Lead markers** - Locations of campaign leads
- **Zone overlays** - Geographic zone boundaries
- **Interaction markers** - Recent interactions (when enabled)
- **Sale markers** - Sales locations (when enabled)

### Lead Clustering

When zoomed out, nearby leads cluster together:

- Clusters show the count of leads
- Click a cluster to zoom in
- Clusters use zone colors when leads are in zones

### Lead Source

Toggle between viewing:

- **Campaign leads** - Only leads in this campaign
- **Account leads** - All leads across the team account

## Zones

### Viewing Zones

Zones appear as colored polygon overlays on the map:

- Each zone has a name and color
- Zone boundaries show the geographic area
- Leads within zones are associated with that zone

### Zone Filtering

Filter the map by zones:

1. Use the zone filter dropdown
1. Select one or more zones
1. The map shows only leads in those zones

### Toggle Zone Display

Turn zone overlays on or off:

- Use the **Show Zones** toggle
- When off, zone boundaries are hidden
- Leads still show their zone colors

